William Barton (16 January 1777 – 7 January 1825) was an English cricketer who played mainly for Middlesex.
He was born at Finsbury in Middlesex in 1777. His known career of 37 first-class cricket matches was from 1795 to 1817. He died at Westminster in London in 1825.
